<TITLE> 400 children fall ill after eating WFP food </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Khagrachhari, June 1 (bdnews24.com)More than four hundred primary school children in Khagrachhari fell ill on Monday after eating biscuits provided by WFP, said local officials. At least 428 students were suffering from food poisoning in two remote upazilas of the district, Laxmichhari and Mohalchhari. Most were admitted to upazila health complexes at Laxmichhari, Manikchhari and Mohalchhari. Some were taken to Chittagong Medical College Hospital. Dr Abu Taher, a civil surgeon of Khagrachhari, told bdnews24.com, "The children are suffering from stomach ache and diarrhea." Laxmichhai upazila chairman Ramrachay Chowdhury said children of Monghapara, Jaindrapara, Debolchhari and Jharolchhari were the worst affected in number. District civil surgeon and deputy commissioner Md Khalilur Rahman and local officials visited the areas. WFP distributes food among primary school children, in partnership with local NGO Kabidang, under a schools feeding programme. bdnews24
